{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17488375","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17488375"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T03:39:13+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T03:39:13+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"424"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"424","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/424"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.12,0.36,0.04,0.05,0.43]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"424"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"108313"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"424","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/424"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"424"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"90716"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"3"},{"type":"tags","id":"20"},{"type":"tags","id":"29"},{"type":"tags","id":"31"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"78"},{"type":"tags","id":"393"},{"type":"tags","id":"1115"},{"type":"tags","id":"4955"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"4992"},{"type":"tags","id":"11629"},{"type":"tags","id":"11642"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"2496"},{"type":"contributions","id":"2522"},{"type":"contributions","id":"16168"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42082"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44755"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"108313","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/108313"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EAn otherwise well 35-year-old man presents with a pigmented lesion on his right shoulder, which has been present for three months. On examination, there is a smooth-surfaced 1 cm diameter pigmented lesion on his shoulder. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe lesion is then excised with a 3 mm margin of normal tissue. Histopathology reveals a melanoma, with a breslow thickness 2.0 mm. It appears to have been completely removed, with normal tissue found at all margins of the excision specimen. The patient is concerned to know if he requires any further treatment.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate advice?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Further excision (5-10 mm margin)","Regular observation only","Wide excision of the tumour site and axillary node clearance","Further excision (2-3 cm margin) and skin grafting","Further excision (2cm) and sentinel node biopsy"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EAll types of melanomas have high malignant potential, and in order to minimise this wide excisional margins are used. Breslow thickness of the melanoma (detected on histological examination by biopsy) guides appropriate excision margins:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EMelanoma in-situ: 5-10mm margin\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThickness \u0026lt;1mm = 1cm margin\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThickness 1-4mm = 1-2cm margin, increasing as thickness increases and with clinical decision\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThickness \u0026gt;4mm = 2cm margin\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe other consideration is a sentinel lymph node (SLN) biopsy, as this will be the first site malignant cells will lodge following metastasis. SLN biopsy is recommended with thickness \u0026gt;1mm and should be done by those with experience.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EStaging of melanoma takes into account the breslow thickness and sentinel node biopsy.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EStage 0 - melanoma in situ\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EStage 1 - breslow thickness up to 1mm and only confined to skin\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EStage 2 - breslow of any thickness and confined to skin (sentinel lymph node biopsy negative)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EStage 3 - melanoma of any thickness + spread to sentinel lymph node or nearby skin\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EStage 4 - spread to internal organ or lymph node not in sentinel chain\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThis patient has a 2.0 mm thick lesion, requiring a \u003Cstrong\u003E1-2cm margin and SLN biopsy\u003C/strong\u003E.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The histological assessment of a locally excised melanoma will determine the need for any further excision and sentinel lymph node biopsy."],"references":["Sladden MJ, Nieweg OE, Howle J, Coventry BJ, Thompson JF. Updated evidence-based clinical practice guidelines for the diagnosis and management of melanoma: definitive excision margins for primary cutaneous melanoma.\u00a0MJA; 2018: 208(3). Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/29438650/","Thompson JF, Scolyer RA, Kefford RF. Melanoma a management guide for GPs. Australian Family Physician. 2012; 41(7): 470-73. Available at: https://www.racgp.org.au/afp/2012/july/melanoma-guide","Pathak S, Zito PM. Clinical Guidelines for the Staging, Diagnosis, and Management of Cutaneous Malignant Melanoma. [Updated 2023 Jun 26]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK572149/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"90716"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"424"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"90716","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/90716"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-07-09T16:40:11+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-07-09T16:40:11+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"424"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"108313"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"3","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/3"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\uddf4","name":"Dermatology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:42+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"20","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/20"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc4c","name":"Plastic Surgery","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"2"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"29","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/29"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udd2c","name":"Pathology","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"4"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"31","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/31"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf97","name":"Oncology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:45+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"66","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/66"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Management","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relatio